Birth vlog?

I was worried my entire pregnancy because I had a very very little bump until I was 30-34 weeks pregnant. I would go in to my appointments and just talk about how I was so worried about her size and how I wasn’t showing. Your bump size has a lot to do with your own body and ab strength. It’s WAY common for first pregnancies to be almost unnoticeable. Because your muscles have never expanded the way pregnancy needs them to. So your muscles are super super tight throughout the entire pregnancy making the bump smaller than the stereotypical pregnant bellies.
